1
00:00:01,335 --> 00:00:04,369
<i>[ Clock Ticking ]</i>               


2
00:00:18,085 --> 00:00:20,084
                    HI, JAROD.  


3
00:00:22,489 --> 00:00:24,489
            MOM?                


4
00:00:26,694 --> 00:00:28,727
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?            


5
00:00:30,497 --> 00:00:32,564
I CAN'T HEAR YOU.               


6
00:00:38,906 --> 00:00:41,172
[ Ringing ]                     


7
00:00:41,241 --> 00:00:43,742
            MOM?                


8
00:00:43,810 --> 00:00:47,111
<i>[ Ticking, Ringing ]</i>            
        MOM?                    


9
00:00:47,180 --> 00:00:49,614
<i>[ Shrill Ringing ]</i>              


10
00:00:49,683 --> 00:00:53,752
<i>[ Broots ] HE'S BEEN CALLING</i>    
<i>EVERY TWO MINUTES LIKE CLOCKWORK</i>
<i>BUT ONLY WANTS TO TALK TO YOU.</i>  


11
00:00:53,821 --> 00:00:56,822
HERE'S YOUR EXTENSION, OKAY?    
I'LL BE RIGHT OVER HERE.        


12
00:00:58,959 --> 00:01:02,361
                    WHAT LINE?  
WELL, DON'T YOU THINK           
WE SHOULD WAIT FOR MISS PARKER? 


13
00:01:02,429 --> 00:01:06,931
- WE'LL DO IT WITHOUT HER.      
- SYDNEY, SHE'S GONNA KILL ME.  


14
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:09,568
                    WHAT LINE?  
OKAY, TWO.                      


15
00:01:09,637 --> 00:01:13,071
BUT KEEP HIM ON AS LONG         
AS YOU CAN. I'VE ALREADY        
INITIATED A TRACE.              


16
00:01:13,140 --> 00:01:15,073
                    [ Beeping ] 


17
00:01:15,142 --> 00:01:17,242
                <i> [ Sydney ]</i>     
                <i> HELLO, JAROD?</i>  


18
00:01:19,312 --> 00:01:22,481
I HAD THE DREAM AGAIN.          
            ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?  


19
00:01:22,549 --> 00:01:24,783
KEEP TALKING TO HIM.            
WE ALMOST GOT HIM.              


20
00:01:27,687 --> 00:01:31,923
- [ Loud Whistling Over Phone ] 
- TELL BROOTS I DISCOVERED      
  RADIO SHACK.                  


21
00:01:36,797 --> 00:01:38,730
    STRANGE.                    


22
00:01:38,798 --> 00:01:41,065
    FEELING HOMESICK.           


23
00:01:43,937 --> 00:01:45,904
        ONLY I DON'T KNOW       
        WHERE HOME IS.          


24
00:01:45,973 --> 00:01:48,340
    YOUR HOME'S HERE, JAROD.    


25
00:01:48,408 --> 00:01:50,975
        YOU WERE NEVER MEANT    
        FOR THE OUTSIDE WORLD.  


26
00:01:51,044 --> 00:01:53,445
SPARE ME THE WHITE-LEOPARD      
SPEECH, SYDNEY.                 


27
00:01:53,513 --> 00:01:55,981
SOMEBODY AT THE CENTRE          
KNOWS WHO I AM.                 


28
00:01:56,049 --> 00:01:58,616
I WANT THE TRUTH.               
    I'M SURE WE CAN EXPLORE...  


29
00:01:58,685 --> 00:02:02,520
            THESE QUESTIONS     
            IF YOU COME BACK    
            AND RESUME OUR WORK.


30
00:02:02,589 --> 00:02:04,589
I WISH I COULD BELIEVE YOU.     


31
00:02:04,658 --> 00:02:08,292
            WHAT YOU BELIEVE    
            OR DON'T BELIEVE    
            IS NOT THE ISSUE.   


32
00:02:08,361 --> 00:02:12,264
    WHAT IS?                    
    THOSE DIGITAL SIMULATIONS   
    YOU STOLE.                  


33
00:02:12,333 --> 00:02:14,833
        THEY CONTAIN THE ONLY   
        EXISTING RECORD...      


34
00:02:14,901 --> 00:02:17,135
        OF OVER 25 YEARS        
         OF RESEARCH.           


35
00:02:17,204 --> 00:02:19,204
            THE CENTRE--        


36
00:02:20,574 --> 00:02:22,507
            I WANT THEM BACK.   


37
00:02:22,576 --> 00:02:26,611
WELL, THEN PERHAPS THEY--       
YOU-- WOULD CONSIDER A TRADE.   


38
00:02:27,848 --> 00:02:30,148
A PIECE OF MY PAST              
FOR A PIECE OF YOURS.           


39
00:02:30,217 --> 00:02:34,052
[ Ringing ]                     


40
00:02:34,120 --> 00:02:36,521
GET BACK TO ME, SYDNEY.         
I'M RUNNING LATE.               


41
00:02:36,590 --> 00:02:39,357
        - LATE FOR WHAT?        
        - JUSTICE.              


42
00:02:44,731 --> 00:02:47,566
        <i> [ Buzzing ]</i>            


43
00:02:53,740 --> 00:02:55,474
            MR. HOLMES?         


44
00:02:57,577 --> 00:02:59,912
            ISAAC.              


45
00:02:59,980 --> 00:03:01,813
<i>MR.</i> DEXTER?                     


46
00:03:01,881 --> 00:03:05,216
            IS SOMETHING WRONG? 
YOU'RE A MAN.                   


47
00:03:05,285 --> 00:03:09,854
            LAST TIME I CHECKED.
BUT YOU DRESS                   
LIKE A WOMAN.                   


48
00:03:09,923 --> 00:03:13,558
        DIDN'T ANYBODY TELL YOU?
NO.                             


49
00:03:13,627 --> 00:03:17,162
        LISTEN. I KNOW YOU DON'T
        KNOW ME, AND I'LL ADMIT 
        I'M A LITTLE DIFFERENT. 


50
00:03:17,231 --> 00:03:21,733
BUT IF YOU DON'T HELP ME,       
THEY'RE GONNA PUT ME AWAY FASTER
THAN YOU CAN SAY CHANEL NO. 5.  


51
00:03:21,802 --> 00:03:25,704
    <i> I DIDN'T DO ANYTHING WRONG.</i>
    <i> THOSE MEN WERE TRYING</i>      
    <i> TO KILL ME.</i>                


52
00:03:25,773 --> 00:03:28,373
        I JUST DEFENDED MYSELF. 


53
00:03:28,442 --> 00:03:32,577
            YOU WALK OUT ON ME, 
            I'M A DEAD MAN.     


54
00:03:32,646 --> 00:03:36,414
DON'T WORRY, MR. DEXTER.        
        <i> [ Patting Shoulder ]</i>   


55
00:03:36,483 --> 00:03:38,416
I'LL STAND UP WITH YOU.         


56
00:03:39,486 --> 00:03:43,021
    THANK YOU.                  
    I KNEW YOU WERE A GOOD MAN. 


57
00:03:43,089 --> 00:03:45,824
                I COULD SEE IT  
                IN YOUR EYES.   
    HERE.                       


58
00:03:45,893 --> 00:03:47,859
YOUR MASCARA'S RUNNING.         


59
00:03:47,928 --> 00:03:49,928
                    OH.         


60
00:03:51,599 --> 00:03:55,801
            SO HOW LONG         
            YOU BEEN A LAWYER?  
ABOUT SEVEN MINUTES.            


61
00:03:58,271 --> 00:04:00,271
                    OH.         


62
00:04:01,674 --> 00:04:05,177
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>               


63
00:04:59,266 --> 00:05:02,134
    [ Indistinct ]              


64
00:05:05,271 --> 00:05:07,705
        <i> JAROD, PLEASE, JOIN US.</i>


65
00:05:07,774 --> 00:05:11,243
<i>WE WANTED TO BE THE FIRST TO</i>    
<i>CONGRATULATE YOU ON YOUR VICTORY</i>
<i>IN COURT THIS MORNING.</i>          


66
00:05:11,311 --> 00:05:14,912
    - IT WAS BEGINNER'S LUCK.   
    -<i> WE HEARD YOUR CLIENT</i>      
     <i> WAS QUITE A LOOKER.</i>       


67
00:05:14,981 --> 00:05:16,982
    JUST HOW LUCKY DID YOU GET? 


68
00:05:17,050 --> 00:05:19,584
<i>DON'T LET BRADLEY</i>               
<i>GET UNDER YOUR SKIN.</i>            


69
00:05:19,652 --> 00:05:23,788
ALL JUNIOR ASSOCIATES GET THROWN
A RINGER THEIR                  
FIRST TIME OUT.                 


70
00:05:23,857 --> 00:05:26,658
THERE'S HONOR IN KEEPING        
POOR, INNOCENT MEN              
OUT OF JAIL.                    


71
00:05:26,726 --> 00:05:30,161
            EVEN IF THEY DO     
            WEAR CHIFFON.       
<i>EXCUSE ME.</i>                      


72
00:05:30,230 --> 00:05:34,832
MR. DUMONT, MICHAEL METZGER'S   
WAITING IN RECEPTION.           
                <i> THANKS, ANNIE.</i> 


73
00:05:34,901 --> 00:05:37,368
    THANKFULLY, A CLIENT        
    WHO'S NEITHER POOR          
    NOR INNOCENT.               


74
00:05:37,437 --> 00:05:40,472
            SPEAKING OF POOR,   
            INNOCENT MEN,       


75
00:05:40,540 --> 00:05:42,874
<i>HAVE YOU FINISHED YOUR BRIEF</i>    
<i>ON THE WHITTAKER APPEAL?</i>        


76
00:05:42,943 --> 00:05:46,645
<i>BEN, I'M SPENDING 70 HOURS</i>      
<i>A WEEK ON THE METZGER MERGER.</i>   


77
00:05:46,713 --> 00:05:48,680
MY PLATE IS FULL.               


78
00:05:48,749 --> 00:05:52,050
        DUMONT IS A PIT BULL    
        IN THE COURT,           
        BUT SOMETIMES FORGETS...


79
00:05:52,118 --> 00:05:54,352
        WHO SIGNS HIS PAYCHECKS.


80
00:05:54,421 --> 00:05:57,222
    [ Chuckles ]                
    ALL RIGHT, I'LL TAKE        
    CARE OF IT.                 


81
00:05:57,291 --> 00:05:59,357
OH, JAROD, IN CASE              
YOU'RE INTERESTED,              


82
00:05:59,426 --> 00:06:03,594
COLLINS DEPARTMENT STORE        
IS HAVING A TWO-FOR-ONE SALE    
ON THE LINGERIE SECTION.        


83
00:06:03,663 --> 00:06:06,064
SEE YA, TIGER.                  
                JAROD, KEEP UP  
                THE GOOD WORK.  


84
00:06:06,133 --> 00:06:09,300
<i>I'LL DO MY BEST, SIR.</i>           
            ANNIE,              


85
00:06:09,369 --> 00:06:11,903
            <i> THERE'S SOMETHING</i>  
            <i> I WANT YOU TO DO.</i>  


86
00:06:11,971 --> 00:06:14,706
BRAD, MAY I SPEAK TO YOU        
FOR A MOMENT?                   
            IT WAS A JOKE.      


87
00:06:14,775 --> 00:06:17,208
I UNDERSTAND THAT. I WANTED     
TO ASK YOU SOME QUESTIONS...    


88
00:06:17,277 --> 00:06:19,444
ABOUT THE WHITTAKER TRIAL.      


89
00:06:21,548 --> 00:06:24,015
    OLD MAN SLOANE LOST A MURDER
    DEFENSE A FEW YEARS AGO,    


90
00:06:24,083 --> 00:06:26,551
            AND I GOT STUCK     
            HOLDING THE BAG.    


91
00:06:26,620 --> 00:06:28,853
WHY WOULD SLOANE TIE UP         
HIS BEST TRIAL ATTORNEY...      


92
00:06:28,922 --> 00:06:31,422
WRITING AN APPEAL THAT COULD    
BE HANDLED BY A FIRST-YEAR      
LAW STUDENT?                    


93
00:06:31,491 --> 00:06:34,258
    THE WHITTAKER CASE IS       
    A RAW NERVE WITH SLOANE.    


94
00:06:34,327 --> 00:06:37,161
            HE HATES TO LOSE.   
LET ME WRITE THE APPEAL.        


95
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:39,897
<i>YOU SAID YOUR PLATE</i>             
<i>IS FULL.</i>                        


96
00:06:39,966 --> 00:06:42,734
AND I COULD USE THE PRACTICE.   


97
00:06:42,803 --> 00:06:47,139
THE OLD MAN WILL HAVE MY HEAD   
IF HE FINDS OUT I DUMPED THIS   
ON A JUNIOR ASSOCIATE.          


98
00:06:47,207 --> 00:06:50,241
    I CAN KEEP A SECRET         
    IF YOU CAN.                 


99
00:06:51,377 --> 00:06:53,311
    LET'S TALK.                 


100
00:06:53,379 --> 00:06:57,449
YOU FIND DUMONT FOR ME NOW,     
OR I'M GONNA FIND HIM MYSELF.   


101
00:06:57,517 --> 00:07:01,319
<i>BASE IT ON MY PREVIOUS APPEALS</i>  
<i>AND KEEP ME IN THE LOOP.</i>        


102
00:07:01,388 --> 00:07:04,255
YOU'RE THE BOSS.                
            NOT YET, BUT        
            I'M WORKING ON IT.  


103
00:07:04,324 --> 00:07:08,092
MR. METZGER. I JUST GOT         
OFF THE PHONE WITH THE JUDGE.   


104
00:07:08,161 --> 00:07:10,962
I THINK EVERYTHING'S GONNA WORK 
OUT JUST THE WAY YOU WANT IT.   
                        GOOD.   


105
00:07:11,031 --> 00:07:13,297
    HAVE YOU LOST WEIGHT?       
                MAYBE A COUPLE--


106
00:07:17,770 --> 00:07:19,704
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>                      
<i>MADAM DIRECTOR,</i>                 


107
00:07:19,773 --> 00:07:24,643
ALL JAROD WANTS                 
IS SOME SMALL PIECE OF HIMSELF, 
OF HIS PAST.                    


108
00:07:24,711 --> 00:07:27,979
I BELIEVE IF WE CAN             
ACCEPT HIS TRADE OFFER,         


109
00:07:28,047 --> 00:07:30,148
IT WOULD GO A LONG WAY          
TOWARDS REESTABLISHING...       


110
00:07:30,216 --> 00:07:32,950
THE KIND OF TRUST I NEED        
TO BRING HIM BACK.              


111
00:07:33,020 --> 00:07:35,686
            WHAT ABOUT S.I.S.?  


112
00:07:35,755 --> 00:07:40,492
WELL, MISS PARKER BELIEVES      
SHE CAN PISTOL-WHIP HER WAY     
INTO ANY RESOLUTION.            


113
00:07:40,561 --> 00:07:43,261
BUT I KNOW JAROD.               
THE HARDER WE CHASE,            


114
00:07:43,329 --> 00:07:45,496
THE HARDER HE'LL RUN.           


115
00:07:45,565 --> 00:07:48,299
    I'LL DISCUSS YOUR PROPOSAL  
    WITH THE TOWER.             


116
00:07:48,368 --> 00:07:50,968
        BUT I MAKE NO PROMISES. 


117
00:08:01,647 --> 00:08:04,048
        OH, DAMN.               


118
00:08:07,553 --> 00:08:10,488
            THE IDEA IS TO GET  
            ALL THE SAME COLORS 
            ON THE SAME SIDE?   


119
00:08:10,557 --> 00:08:12,857
[ Scoffs ]                      
WHERE WERE YOU                  
DURING THE '80s?                


120
00:08:12,926 --> 00:08:15,159
    I LED A VERY ISOLATED LIFE. 


121
00:08:15,228 --> 00:08:17,495
WHEN DID YOU QUIT SMOKING?      


122
00:08:17,564 --> 00:08:19,564
HOW DID YOU KNOW THAT?          


123
00:08:19,632 --> 00:08:22,433
OH, YOUR TREMBLING HANDS,       


124
00:08:22,502 --> 00:08:25,069
            <i> NICOTINE STAINS</i>    
            <i> ON YOUR FINGERTIPS,</i>
            <i> IRRITABILITY.</i>      


125
00:08:25,138 --> 00:08:29,073
YOU KNOW, YOU CAN TRY           
A SIMPLE EPSOM SALT BATH.       


126
00:08:29,142 --> 00:08:32,010
THE SALT, IT DRAWS THE TAR      
AND NICOTINE OUT OF THE         
BLOODSTREAM THROUGH THE SKIN.   


127
00:08:32,078 --> 00:08:34,979
SO, YOU'RE A DOCTOR             
AND A LAWYER?                   


128
00:08:35,048 --> 00:08:38,015
                AND I'M WORKING 
                ON INDIAN CHIEF.
ANNIE.                          


129
00:08:38,084 --> 00:08:42,320
WOULD YOU PLEASE TRANSCRIBE,    
PROOF AND HAND-DELIVER THESE    
TO MY BOAT TONIGHT?             


130
00:08:42,389 --> 00:08:46,358
        TONIGHT? OH, NO, NO, NO.
        MR. SLOANE, I CAN'T,    
        BECAUSE MY DAUGHTER--   


131
00:08:46,426 --> 00:08:51,630
IS A VERY LOVELY GIRL           
WHO KNOWS HOW VALUABLE          
HER MOTHER IS TO THIS FIRM.     


132
00:08:51,698 --> 00:08:54,633
<i>ANNIE'S THE BEST, JAROD.</i>        


133
00:08:58,438 --> 00:09:00,939
    ANNIE DO THIS.              
     ANNIE DO THAT.             


134
00:09:01,007 --> 00:09:05,343
I'LL TELL YOU-- IT'S LIKE       
BEING SLOANE'S WIFE WITHOUT     
THE FRINGE BENEFITS.            


135
00:09:05,412 --> 00:09:08,946
<i>TOO BAD PAYCHECKS</i>               
<i>ARE HARDER TO QUIT</i>              
<i>THAN CIGARETTES.</i>                


136
00:09:09,015 --> 00:09:12,283
SO, DID YOU NEED                
SOMETHING TOO?                  


137
00:09:12,352 --> 00:09:15,053
    ACTUALLY, BRADLEY DUMONT    
    ASKED ME TO GO OVER         
    AN OLD CASE FILE.           


138
00:09:15,121 --> 00:09:17,055
    MARCUS WHITTAKER?           


139
00:09:17,124 --> 00:09:21,126
OH, YEAH. MR. SLOANE            
HAD THOSE FILES MOVED           
DOWN TO THE BASEMENT.           


140
00:09:21,194 --> 00:09:24,829
BUT I'M GONNA WARN YOU.         
IT IS IMPOSSIBLE TO FIND        
ANYTHING DOWN THERE.            


141
00:09:24,897 --> 00:09:26,831
    NOTHING'S IMPOSSIBLE.       


142
00:10:21,154 --> 00:10:23,421
                        <i> JAROD.</i> 


143
00:10:23,490 --> 00:10:25,423
ISAAC, WHAT ARE YOU             
DOING HERE?                     


144
00:10:25,492 --> 00:10:27,892
            I GOT TO THINKING   
            HOW NICE YOU WERE,  
            HOW DECENT.         


145
00:10:27,961 --> 00:10:31,128
        AND I WANTED TO REPAY   
        YOUR KINDNESS.          
        REPAY?                  


146
00:10:32,132 --> 00:10:34,365
<i>MY CHARIOT.</i>                     
            <i> ISAAC!</i>             


147
00:10:34,434 --> 00:10:36,700
IT'S BEAUTIFUL.                 
                [ Chuckles ]    


148
00:10:36,769 --> 00:10:39,470
        IT'LL BE MORE BEAUTIFUL 
        AFTER 37 PAYMENTS.      


149
00:10:39,539 --> 00:10:42,239
    THAT'S WHEN I PLAN TO TRADE 
    IT IN FOR A LIMOUSINE.      


150
00:10:42,308 --> 00:10:45,376
        ACTUALLY, I OFFER       
        A VERY VALUABLE SERVICE.


151
00:10:45,445 --> 00:10:48,979
    YOU'D BE SURPRISED HOW MANY 
    CABDRIVERS WON'T PICK UP    
    A MAN IN A DRESS.           


152
00:10:49,048 --> 00:10:52,650
REALLY? WHY?                    


153
00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:56,887
            THE TRUTH IS,       
            I'D LIKE TO OFFER   
            MY SERVICES...      


154
00:10:56,956 --> 00:10:59,257
    AS YOUR PERSONAL CHAUFFEUR. 


155
00:11:00,327 --> 00:11:04,095
            NO KIDDING!         
            WELL, THAT'S GREAT. 


156
00:11:05,832 --> 00:11:09,000
        NOW, YOU SURE YOU HAVE  
        A DRIVER'S LICENSE?     
DON'T WORRY, BOSS.              


157
00:11:09,069 --> 00:11:11,035
YOU'RE IN GOOD HANDS.           


158
00:11:11,104 --> 00:11:13,771
        AND I PROMISE TO BE     
        THE PERFECT LADY.       


159
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:15,807
<i>[ Horn Honking ]</i>                
<i>[ Man Laughing ]</i>                
<i>HEY, BABY!</i>                      


160
00:11:15,875 --> 00:11:19,110
        UP YOURS, PAL!          
<i>[ Tires Screeching ]</i>            


161
00:11:33,827 --> 00:11:35,827
            [ Computer Rings ]  


162
00:11:38,331 --> 00:11:41,132
        VERY GOOD.              


163
00:11:41,201 --> 00:11:44,234
                <i> SYDNEY, A WORD?</i>


164
00:12:01,688 --> 00:12:04,889
    DO YOU WANNA TELL ME        
    WHAT'S GOING ON?            
            <i> NOTHING, REALLY.</i>   


165
00:12:04,958 --> 00:12:07,992
        AN ALPHA BRAIN WAVE     
        EXPERIMENT.             


166
00:12:08,060 --> 00:12:11,629
    <i> QUITE PROMISING, ACTUALLY.</i> 
    THAT'S NOT WHAT I MEAN,     
    AND YOU KNOW IT.            


167
00:12:12,699 --> 00:12:14,899
            YOU SPOKE           
            TO THE DIRECTOR?    


168
00:12:14,968 --> 00:12:17,335
    ANSWER THE QUESTION!        


169
00:12:17,403 --> 00:12:20,939
- JAROD WANTS TO MAKE A DEAL.   
- A DEAL.                       


170
00:12:21,007 --> 00:12:23,107
    HE WANTS TO FIND OUT        
    THE TRUTH OR PART OF IT.    


171
00:12:23,176 --> 00:12:26,644
        <i> IT IS THE HUMANE THING</i> 
        <i> TO DO.</i>                 


172
00:12:26,713 --> 00:12:30,681
YOU ARE OUT OF LINE             
LECTURING ANYBODY               
ABOUT HUMANITY.                 


173
00:12:30,750 --> 00:12:32,850
I'M NOT THE ONE WHO KEPT        
JAROD LOCKED UP                 
FOR 30 YEARS.                   


174
00:12:32,919 --> 00:12:35,253
<i>I'M KILLING</i>                     
<i>YOUR DEAL, SYDNEY.</i>              


175
00:12:35,321 --> 00:12:38,122
    AND THEN I'M GONNA          
    FIND JAROD.                 


176
00:12:39,926 --> 00:12:42,693
AND I'M GONNA END THIS THING    
ONCE AND FOR ALL.               


177
00:13:23,136 --> 00:13:25,670
EVERYBODY'S A CRITIC.           


178
00:13:26,773 --> 00:13:29,073
<i>♪♪ [ Blues ]</i>                    


179
00:13:29,142 --> 00:13:32,243
        DOESN'T THIS MUSIC      
        JUST GIVE YOU CHILLS UP 
        AND DOWN YOUR SPINE?    


180
00:13:32,311 --> 00:13:35,246
IT'S VERY... SAD.               


181
00:13:35,314 --> 00:13:37,348
        IT'S THE BLUES, BABY.   


182
00:13:37,417 --> 00:13:40,017
    THE BLUES.                  


183
00:13:40,086 --> 00:13:42,319
I LIKE IT.                      
            IT'S ABOUT LIFE,    


184
00:13:42,388 --> 00:13:45,089
            ABOUT PAIN--        
            IT'S ABOUT TRUTH.   


185
00:13:45,158 --> 00:13:48,359
TRUTH IS GOOD.                  
            YEAH. LOOK AT ME,   
            FOR EXAMPLE.        


186
00:13:48,428 --> 00:13:51,329
                I COME OUT HERE 
                EVERY DAY       
                LIKE A TARGET.  


187
00:13:51,398 --> 00:13:54,565
    AND I SAY TO THE WORLD,     
    "HA!                        


188
00:13:54,634 --> 00:13:58,069
    THIS IS ME.                 
    TAKE IT OR LEAVE IT."       


189
00:13:58,137 --> 00:14:01,405
CAN I ASK YOU A QUESTION?       
                WHY DO I DRESS  
                LIKE THIS?      


190
00:14:01,474 --> 00:14:03,907
WELL, IT DOES SEEM              
TO DRAW ATTENTION.              


191
00:14:03,976 --> 00:14:07,511
    I DON'T KNOW WHY I DO IT.   
    I JUST KNOW IT'S RIGHT      
    FOR ME.                     


192
00:14:07,580 --> 00:14:09,614
        I MEAN, I GREW UP LIKE  
        EVERYBODY ELSE.         


193
00:14:09,683 --> 00:14:12,750
        I PLAYED FOOTBALL,      
        DATED A CHEERLEADER.    


194
00:14:12,819 --> 00:14:15,752
    BUT I NEVER FELT COMPLETE   
    UNTIL I FOUND THIS.         


195
00:14:15,821 --> 00:14:18,956
    <i> IT HASN'T BEEN EASY THOUGH.</i>


196
00:14:19,025 --> 00:14:21,859
WHY DO IT THEN?                 
                <i> IT'S WHO I AM.</i> 


197
00:14:21,928 --> 00:14:24,895
PEOPLE CAN'T GO AROUND          
ACTING LIKE THEY'RE SOMETHING   
THEY AREN'T.                    


198
00:14:24,964 --> 00:14:28,933
    YOU DO THAT LONG ENOUGH,    
    AND PRETTY SOON YOU CAN'T   
    FIND YOURSELF ANYMORE.      


199
00:14:29,002 --> 00:14:31,636
    KNOW WHAT I MEAN?           


200
00:14:32,839 --> 00:14:34,839
    YEAH.                       


201
00:15:26,359 --> 00:15:29,194
    SO, WHO WE LOOKIN' FOR?     


202
00:15:29,262 --> 00:15:31,028
            <i> [ Buzzer Sounding ]</i>


203
00:15:31,097 --> 00:15:33,932
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>HIS NAME IS MARCUS WHITTAKER.</i>   


204
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:38,169
        - FRIEND OF YOURS?      
        - NOT EXACTLY.          


205
00:15:38,237 --> 00:15:40,371
                <i> [ Isaac ]</i>      
                <i> WHAT'D HE DO?</i>  


206
00:15:41,741 --> 00:15:43,741
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>NOTHING.</i>                        


207
00:15:47,147 --> 00:15:49,180
    NOTHING AT ALL.             


208
00:15:59,959 --> 00:16:03,561
THE TOWER HAS CONSIDERED ALL    
THE VARIABLES AND HAS DECIDED   
TO MOVE FORWARD WITH THE DEAL.  


209
00:16:03,630 --> 00:16:07,232
- YOU CAN'T BE SERIOUS.         
- I THINK YOU KNOW THAT I AM.   


210
00:16:07,300 --> 00:16:10,034
THE CHAIRMAN IS GOING           
TO HEAR ABOUT THIS.             


211
00:16:10,103 --> 00:16:13,704
        YOUR FATHER CAST        
        THE DECIDING VOTE.      


212
00:16:13,773 --> 00:16:17,475
<i>THE INFORMATION JAROD REQUESTED</i> 
<i>WILL BE ON YOUR DESK</i>            
<i>WITHIN THE HOUR.</i>                


213
00:16:17,544 --> 00:16:20,244
    -<i> USE IT WISELY.</i>            
    -<i> [ Elevator Bell Dings ]</i>   


214
00:16:25,318 --> 00:16:28,720
[ Sydney ] YOU'LL ONLY HAVE ONE 
SHOT AT THE TERRORIST, JAROD.   
I HAD THE DREAM AGAIN.          


215
00:16:28,789 --> 00:16:33,124
IT'S JUST A DREAM, JAROD.       
FORGET ABOUT IT                 
AND CONCENTRATE.                


216
00:16:33,192 --> 00:16:35,526
    IS IT POSSIBLE...           


217
00:16:35,595 --> 00:16:39,263
    TO FORGET WHO YOU ARE       
    AND WHERE YOU CAME FROM?    


218
00:16:39,332 --> 00:16:42,800
    JAROD, PLEASE.              


219
00:16:42,869 --> 00:16:47,504
IT'S JUST THAT IN THIS DREAM,   
I CAN'T SEE MY MOTHER'S FACE.   


220
00:16:47,573 --> 00:16:49,907
            SHE'S IN THE YARD   
            HANGING WASH.       


221
00:16:49,976 --> 00:16:52,677
ONE SHOT, JAROD.                
TIME'S RUNNING OUT.             


222
00:16:52,746 --> 00:16:54,879
THE HOSTAGES                    
ARE COUNTING ON YOU.            


223
00:16:54,948 --> 00:16:57,948
BUT I WANNA SEE HER, SYDNEY.    
I WANNA SEE MY MOTHER'S FACE!   


224
00:16:58,017 --> 00:17:00,818
FINISH THE SIMULATION           
AND I'LL SEE TO IT THAT YOU DO. 


225
00:17:00,887 --> 00:17:04,288
                    PROMISE?    
PROMISE.                        


226
00:17:10,563 --> 00:17:14,432
        WAIT. I CAN'T           
        COMPLETE THE MISSION.   


227
00:17:14,501 --> 00:17:16,634
I MIGHT HIT A HOSTAGE.          


228
00:17:16,703 --> 00:17:19,770
I MIGHT KILL                    
AN INNOCENT PERSON.             
            SOMETIMES, JAROD,   


229
00:17:19,839 --> 00:17:23,708
<i>ONE LIFE MUST BE SACRIFICED</i>     
<i>IN ORDER TO SAVE OTHERS.</i>        


230
00:17:27,213 --> 00:17:29,380
            <i> [ Machine Beeps ]</i>  
                <i> [ Video Stops ]</i>


231
00:17:53,072 --> 00:17:55,606
[ Woman Reporter ]              
MURDER SUSPECT                  
MARCUS WHITTAKER,               


232
00:17:55,675 --> 00:17:58,476
ACCUSED OF BEATING AUDREY PRICE 
TO DEATH IN HER APARTMENT,      


233
00:17:58,545 --> 00:18:01,446
WAS ARRESTED IN                 
THE EARLY MORNING HOURS         
IN HIS JANITOR QUARTERS...      


234
00:18:01,514 --> 00:18:03,747
OF THIS WEST L.A.               
APARTMENT BUILDING.             


235
00:18:03,816 --> 00:18:06,951
MARCUS WHITTAKER HAS AN UNUSUAL 
BENEFACTOR IN THIS CASE--       


236
00:18:07,020 --> 00:18:09,987
HIS EMPLOYER, REAL ESTATE       
MAGNATE MICHAEL METZGER,        


237
00:18:10,056 --> 00:18:13,991
WHOSE COMPANY OWNS              
THE BUILDING IN WHICH           
THE MURDER TOOK PLACE.          


238
00:18:17,430 --> 00:18:19,664
            HOW LONG WE GONNA   
            STAY HERE?          


239
00:18:21,434 --> 00:18:23,835
            HELLO?              


240
00:18:23,903 --> 00:18:26,371
    <i> AUDREY PRICE'S DEATH</i>       
    <i> IS A TRAGEDY.</i>              


241
00:18:26,439 --> 00:18:29,140
BUT MARCUS WHITTAKER SHOULDN'T  
BE FORCED TO TAKE THE RAP...    


242
00:18:29,209 --> 00:18:31,509
    FOR THE SLOPPY HANDLING     
    OF THIS INVESTIGATION.      


243
00:18:31,577 --> 00:18:35,312
    I'M JUST GRATEFUL           
    THAT BEN SLOANE HAS AGREED  
    TO REPRESENT MARCUS.        


244
00:18:35,381 --> 00:18:38,750
    MR. METZGER WAS WITH ME     
    ON MY BOAT WHEN WORD        
    REACHED HIM...              


245
00:18:38,818 --> 00:18:41,686
        THAT A MURDER           
        HAD TAKEN PLACE ON      
        ONE OF HIS PROPERTIES.  


246
00:18:41,755 --> 00:18:45,089
        NATURALLY, I OFFERED    
        MY SERVICES.            


247
00:18:45,158 --> 00:18:48,759
ISAAC, LET'S GO SHOPPING.       


248
00:18:48,828 --> 00:18:51,462
    WHOO! NOW YOU'RE TALKING    
    MY LANGUAGE.                


249
00:19:01,841 --> 00:19:03,775
                <i> [ Man ]</i>        
                <i> IT'S CREEPY.</i>   


250
00:19:03,843 --> 00:19:06,244
            HE'S BEEN DOING THAT
            FOR ALMOST AN HOUR. 


251
00:19:09,381 --> 00:19:12,417
    CHECK OUT HIS GIRLFRIEND.   


252
00:19:14,988 --> 00:19:18,756
    - ARE THESE ALL             
      THE BOAT SHOES YOU HAVE?  
    - YES, SIR.                 


253
00:19:19,826 --> 00:19:21,759
    I'LL TAKE THEM ALL.         


254
00:19:21,828 --> 00:19:24,595
            YOU WANT SEVEN PAIRS
            OF BOAT SHOES?      


255
00:19:24,664 --> 00:19:28,833
- MM-HMM.                       
- DO YOU CARRY THESE IN A 13?   


256
00:19:32,105 --> 00:19:34,105
                <i> [ Knocking ]</i>   


257
00:19:49,088 --> 00:19:51,589
            WELL?               


258
00:19:51,657 --> 00:19:54,158
    I DID IT.                   
    JUST LIKE YOU SAID.         


259
00:19:54,226 --> 00:19:56,160
            AND?                


260
00:19:56,229 --> 00:19:59,030
    I DRAGGED IT AROUND         
    BEHIND MY BIKE.             


261
00:19:59,098 --> 00:20:01,699
        - EXCELLENT.            
        - [ Scoffs ]            


262
00:20:01,768 --> 00:20:04,602
        OH, YES, RIGHT.         
        FIVE DOLLARS.           


263
00:20:04,670 --> 00:20:06,704
    THAT'S RIGHT.               


264
00:20:08,407 --> 00:20:13,343
I HAVE FRIENDS. WE COULD        
REALLY MESS UP YOUR CAR         
IF YOU'RE INTERESTED.           


265
00:20:13,412 --> 00:20:15,379
        I'LL LET YOU KNOW.      


266
00:20:15,448 --> 00:20:17,014
            COOL.               


267
00:20:32,766 --> 00:20:35,700
MR. WHITTAKER IS THE ONLY       
POSSIBLE PERPETRATOR.           


268
00:20:35,768 --> 00:20:38,702
THE DEFENSE HAS NO RELEVANT     
EVIDENCE TO THE CONTRARY.       


269
00:20:47,980 --> 00:20:50,848
<i>YOU'RE WRONG, MR. EDWARDS.</i>      


270
00:20:52,251 --> 00:20:55,052
<i>[ Edwards ]</i>                     
<i>THANK YOU. ENJOY THE BOOK.</i>      


271
00:20:58,057 --> 00:21:02,160
MY GOD. WHAT DID YOU DO,        
DRAG THIS BEHIND A CAR?         


272
00:21:02,228 --> 00:21:05,763
        WELL, ACTUALLY, I PAID  
        A KID TO DRAG IT        
        BEHIND HIS BIKE.        


273
00:21:05,832 --> 00:21:08,933
    - TRUTHFULLY, IT'S BEEN     
      LIKE A BIBLE TO ME.       
    - WELL, I'M FLATTERED.      


274
00:21:09,002 --> 00:21:12,803
WHOM SHOULD I MAKE              
THIS OUT TO?                    
            JOHN COREY, JR.     


275
00:21:12,872 --> 00:21:15,739
I KNEW A JOHN COREY             
AT DARTMOUTH. YOU'RE NOT--      


276
00:21:15,808 --> 00:21:19,276
    GUILTY. DAD'S BEEN AFTER ME 
    TO LOOK YOU UP FOR YEARS.   


277
00:21:19,345 --> 00:21:23,715
<i>SO THERE'S YOUR FATHER WEARING</i>  
<i>NOTHING BUT A DRUNKEN GRIN</i>      
<i>RUNNING UP THE DORM HALLWAY...</i>  


278
00:21:23,783 --> 00:21:26,150
            SHOUTING, "BANZAI!" 


279
00:21:26,218 --> 00:21:28,386
DEAR OLD DAD.                   
                    YEAH.       


280
00:21:28,454 --> 00:21:31,589
        I NEVER SAW A BETTER    
        LITIGATOR IN MY LIFE.   


281
00:21:31,658 --> 00:21:33,590
HE SAID THE SAME THING          
ABOUT YOU.                      


282
00:21:33,659 --> 00:21:37,094
I ESPECIALLY ADMIRED THE WAY    
YOU BROUGHT DOWN BEN SLOANE     
A FEW YEARS AGO.                


283
00:21:37,163 --> 00:21:40,965
<i>THE WHITTAKER</i>                   
<i>TRIAL?</i>                          
    OH. SLOANE HAD NO CASE.     


284
00:21:41,034 --> 00:21:43,901
    REALLY? WHAT ABOUT          
    THE SHOE PRINT?             


285
00:21:45,572 --> 00:21:48,138
    HOW'D YOU KNOW ABOUT THAT?  
<i>I DID A PAPER,</i>                  


286
00:21:48,207 --> 00:21:50,708
<i> THE PEOPLE VS. WHITTAKER,</i>      
 AT UCLA. I READ THE CASE FILES.


287
00:21:50,776 --> 00:21:55,313
    - 5,000 PAGES?              
    - 5,612 TO BE EXACT.        


288
00:21:58,418 --> 00:22:02,653
    MICHAEL METZGER BUYS        
    WHITTAKER THE MOST EXPENSIVE
    LAWYER IN THE CITY,         


289
00:22:02,722 --> 00:22:04,722
                AND THE GUY     
                DROPS THE BALL. 


290
00:22:04,790 --> 00:22:08,626
            <i> WE COULDN'T BELIEVE</i>
            <i> HE MISSED IT.</i>      
THE D.A. KNEW ABOUT THE PRINT?  


291
00:22:08,695 --> 00:22:10,828
                WE PROVIDED IT  
                IN DISCOVERY.   


292
00:22:10,897 --> 00:22:14,798
    WE KEPT WAITING FOR SLOANE  
    TO PLAY THE CARD,           
    TO CREATE DOUBT.            


293
00:22:14,867 --> 00:22:16,901
            <i> BUT IT NEVER CAME.</i> 


294
00:22:16,970 --> 00:22:18,969
AND YOU NEVER SAID ANYTHING?    


295
00:22:19,038 --> 00:22:21,004
            [ Sighs ]           
            WE HAD WITNESSES... 


296
00:22:21,073 --> 00:22:24,341
<i>WHO SAID THAT MARCUS WHITTAKER</i>  
<i>WAS OBSESSED WITH AUDREY PRICE.</i> 


297
00:22:24,410 --> 00:22:26,977
        HIS PRINTS WERE         
        ALL OVER THE APARTMENT. 


298
00:22:27,046 --> 00:22:31,014
<i>HE WAS CAUGHT IN HIS JANITOR'S</i>  
<i>QUARTERS CLEANING HER BLOOD</i>     
<i>OFF HIS CLOTHES.</i>                


299
00:22:31,084 --> 00:22:33,784
NOW, YOU DON'T HAVE TO READ     
PROUST TO CONNECT THOSE DOTS.   


300
00:22:33,853 --> 00:22:36,820
    YET YOU NEVER FOUND         
    A MURDER WEAPON.            


301
00:22:37,891 --> 00:22:39,823
        MARCUS WHITTAKER        
        WAS GUILTY OF MURDER.   


302
00:22:39,892 --> 00:22:44,262
    <i> BEN SLOANE WAS JUST GUILTY</i> 
    <i> OF BEING A BAD LAWYER.</i>     


303
00:22:44,330 --> 00:22:47,031
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>MR. SLOANE CAME TO</i>              
<i>THE POLICE STATION.</i>             


304
00:22:48,934 --> 00:22:52,703
HE WAS NICE TO ME.              
 HE BROUGHT ME A HAM SANDWICH.  


305
00:22:54,507 --> 00:22:56,507
        WHAT ARE YOU MAKING?    


306
00:22:56,576 --> 00:22:58,576
        PAPER CLOCKS.           


307
00:22:59,779 --> 00:23:03,213
A PEN PAL TAUGHT ME.            
THEY REALLY WORK.               


308
00:23:03,283 --> 00:23:06,250
THEY'D BE BETTER                
WITH NOTE CARDS.                


309
00:23:06,319 --> 00:23:09,286
THE-THE PAPER THE GUARDS        
GIVE ME GETS ALL SOFT.          


310
00:23:10,856 --> 00:23:14,826
    - WOULD THESE DO?           
    - CAN I HAVE THOSE?         


311
00:23:16,395 --> 00:23:18,396
                        SURE.   


312
00:23:21,568 --> 00:23:25,703
        MARCUS, I WANNA ASK YOU 
        SOME QUESTIONS          
        ABOUT YOUR CASE.        


313
00:23:25,772 --> 00:23:28,238
MR. SLOANE IS MY LAWYER.        


314
00:23:28,307 --> 00:23:31,542
    I KNOW, BUT I'M HERE        
    TO HELP HIM, AND YOU.       


315
00:23:31,610 --> 00:23:33,344
                OKAY?           


316
00:23:34,680 --> 00:23:37,681
    OKAY.                       
            <i> CAN YOU TELL ME...</i> 


317
00:23:37,750 --> 00:23:41,552
WHY YOU RAN AWAY THE NIGHT      
THAT AUDREY PRICE WAS KILLED?   


318
00:23:41,621 --> 00:23:43,687
    I DIDN'T WANNA              
    GO TO JAIL AGAIN.           


319
00:23:43,756 --> 00:23:48,692
YOU HAD GOTTEN INTO SOME TROUBLE
WHEN YOU LIVED WITH YOUR MOTHER,
IS THAT CORRECT?                


320
00:23:48,761 --> 00:23:51,762
SOME BOYS WERE MAKING           
FUN OF HER.                     


321
00:23:51,830 --> 00:23:53,897
<i>I HAD TO FIGHT 'EM.</i>             


322
00:23:55,368 --> 00:23:57,768
    I DIDN'T WANNA              
    HURT ANYONE.                


323
00:23:59,138 --> 00:24:01,572
<i>I HAD TO GO LIVE AT MILLTOWN.</i>   


324
00:24:01,641 --> 00:24:04,107
        THE DETENTION FACILITY. 


325
00:24:05,945 --> 00:24:09,413
            NOW I WANNA ASK YOU 
            ABOUT THE NIGHT     
            OF THE MURDER.      


326
00:24:12,519 --> 00:24:14,751
    [ Exhales ]                 


327
00:24:14,821 --> 00:24:17,621
I WAS BRINGING FLOWERS          
TO MISS PRICE,                  


328
00:24:17,690 --> 00:24:19,890
LIKE I DID EVERY DAY.           


329
00:24:19,959 --> 00:24:22,326
<i>I WAS FINISHING UP LATE.</i>        


330
00:24:22,394 --> 00:24:25,997
<i>SHE WOULD ALWAYS PAY ME</i>         
<i>AN EXTRA TWO DOLLARS FOR THEM.</i>  


331
00:24:28,501 --> 00:24:32,102
    [ Clears Throat ]           
    BUT THIS TIME,              
    WHEN I WALKED IN,           


332
00:24:32,171 --> 00:24:34,605
I SAW HER BODY ON THE FLOOR.    


333
00:24:38,444 --> 00:24:41,279
            MARCUS? MARCUS?     


334
00:24:41,347 --> 00:24:44,448
            IT'S OKAY. YOU DON'T
            HAVE TO BE AFRAID.  


335
00:24:47,186 --> 00:24:49,720
SHE WAS ALL TWISTED UP.         


336
00:24:49,788 --> 00:24:51,755
HER FACE WAS COVERED            
WITH BLOOD.                     


337
00:24:55,494 --> 00:24:58,462
    THE-- THE OWL               
    WAS SITTING BESIDE HER.     


338
00:24:58,531 --> 00:25:00,931
            THE OWL?            


339
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:04,234
        MADE OF ROCK.           
        IT WAS GREEN.           


340
00:25:04,303 --> 00:25:06,704
    MISS PRICE HAD              
    A WHOLE FAMILY OF THEM.     


341
00:25:06,772 --> 00:25:10,474
    SHE KEPT THEM ON TOP        
    OF HER COFFEE TABLE.        


342
00:25:10,543 --> 00:25:12,510
<i>SHE LOOKED SO QUIET.</i>            


343
00:25:13,680 --> 00:25:17,648
LIKE SHE WAS SLEEPING,          
EXCEPT FOR THE BLOOD.           


344
00:25:19,552 --> 00:25:22,519
                YOU LIKED HER.  
SHE WAS NICE TO ME.             


345
00:25:25,324 --> 00:25:28,092
THE OTHER LAWYER SAID           
I WANTED TO TOUCH HER,          


346
00:25:28,160 --> 00:25:30,861
BUT I JUST THOUGHT              
SHE WAS NICE.                   


347
00:25:33,499 --> 00:25:37,501
        DID YOU EVER NOTICE HER 
        HAVING VISITORS?        


348
00:25:37,570 --> 00:25:40,404
                <i> BOYFRIENDS?</i>    


349
00:25:40,473 --> 00:25:45,175
MR. METZGER WOULD COME          
VISIT HER AT LUNCHTIME          
ALMOST EVERY DAY.               


350
00:25:45,244 --> 00:25:47,311
                MR. METZGER?    
YEAH.                           


351
00:25:47,380 --> 00:25:50,814
HE HAD A COOL BLACK CAR.        


352
00:25:50,884 --> 00:25:55,119
IT HAD REAL SHINY WHEELS ON IT  
AND THE TOP WAS GONE.           
                        MARCUS. 


353
00:25:55,188 --> 00:26:00,191
    DID YOU EVER TELL MR. SLOANE
    OR THE POLICE ABOUT         
    MR. METZGER'S VISITS?       


354
00:26:00,259 --> 00:26:03,294
OH, MR. SLOANE SAID             
THAT I SHOULDN'T SAY NOTHING.   


355
00:26:03,362 --> 00:26:05,896
<i>IT MIGHT NOT LOOK GOOD.</i>         


356
00:26:05,964 --> 00:26:09,132
MR. SLOANE ALWAYS               
LOOKS OUT FOR ME.               


357
00:26:12,305 --> 00:26:14,638
    THEY REALLY WORK.           


358
00:26:39,732 --> 00:26:43,800
                [ Line Ringing ]
IT'S 9:20, AND MICHAEL METZGER  
HAS JUST KILLED A WOMAN.        


359
00:26:43,869 --> 00:26:47,271
WHO DOES HE CALL?               
YOU'VE REACHED BENJAMIN SLOANE  
AT THE MARINA.                  


360
00:26:47,340 --> 00:26:51,875
I WISH I WAS ON MY BOAT         
RIGHT NOW, BUT I'M PROBABLY IN  
MY OFFICE WORKING TO PAY FOR IT.


361
00:26:51,944 --> 00:26:54,445
    LEAVE YOUR NAME AND NUMBER  
    AND I'LL GET BACK TO YOU.   


362
00:26:54,513 --> 00:26:56,747
            [ Machine Beeps ]   


363
00:27:04,857 --> 00:27:08,759
    I DON'T UNDERSTAND.         
    WHY WOULD A DEFENSE LAWYER  
    LIKE MR. SLOANE...          


364
00:27:08,828 --> 00:27:11,362
    <i> PUT A POOR, INNOCENT MAN</i>   
    <i> IN JAIL?</i>                   


365
00:27:15,368 --> 00:27:17,368
        TO KEEP A RICH,         
        GUILTY ONE OUT.         


366
00:27:27,780 --> 00:27:29,747
<i>[ Clock Ticking ]</i>               


367
00:27:34,887 --> 00:27:36,887
                    HI, JAROD.  


368
00:27:38,557 --> 00:27:40,824
[ Ringing ]                     


369
00:27:40,893 --> 00:27:44,094
            MOM?                


370
00:27:44,162 --> 00:27:46,796
<i>[ Ringing Continues ]</i>           
        MOM?                    


371
00:27:52,004 --> 00:27:55,372
    TIME'S UP, SYDNEY.          
    I NEED AN ANSWER.           


372
00:27:55,440 --> 00:27:57,441
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>                      
<i>MISS PARKER'S NOT HAPPY.</i>        


373
00:27:57,509 --> 00:27:59,576
<i>IN FACT, SHE'S REMOVED HERSELF</i>  
<i>FROM THIS CASE...</i>               


374
00:27:59,645 --> 00:28:02,412
<i>BECAUSE THE CENTRE HAS AGREED</i>   
<i>TO YOUR REQUEST, JAROD.</i>         


375
00:28:02,481 --> 00:28:05,382
    YOUR INFORMATION IN RETURN  
    FOR THE STOLEN DISKS.       


376
00:28:05,451 --> 00:28:07,151
    THEY SAID THAT?             


377
00:28:07,220 --> 00:28:09,953
            WE-- YOU AND I--    


378
00:28:10,022 --> 00:28:14,925
    HAVE GUARANTEES             
    FROM THE COUNCIL CHAIRMAN   
    AND THE DIRECTOR.           


379
00:28:16,161 --> 00:28:18,095
    I'M SENDING IT THROUGH NOW. 


380
00:28:18,163 --> 00:28:20,898
    HOPE THIS IS WHAT           
    YOU NEED, JAROD.            


381
00:28:20,967 --> 00:28:23,834
            [ Computer Rings ]  


382
00:28:29,875 --> 00:28:33,710
IS THIS HER, SYDNEY?            
 IS THIS MY MOTHER?             


383
00:28:33,779 --> 00:28:36,614
        YES, IT IS.             


384
00:28:36,682 --> 00:28:41,418
I'LL-I'LL MEET YOU AT THE PLACE 
AND TIME WE AGREED ON EARLIER.  


385
00:28:57,103 --> 00:29:02,173
MR. SLOANE, IS IT TRUE          
THAT YOUR CLIENT WILL NOT BE    
TESTIFYING IN HIS OWN DEFENSE?  


386
00:29:02,241 --> 00:29:05,042
MR. WHITTAKER SUFFERS FROM      
A SEVERE LEARNING DISABILITY.   


387
00:29:05,111 --> 00:29:08,978
IT WAS HIS FEELING AND MINE     
THAT IT WAS NOT IN HIS          
BEST INTEREST TO TAKE THE STAND.


388
00:29:09,047 --> 00:29:13,550
<i>[ Reporter ]</i>                    
<i>WELL, WHAT IS YOUR ASSESSMENT OF</i>
<i>THE PROSECUTION'S CASE SO FAR?</i>  


389
00:29:13,618 --> 00:29:17,020
I THINK THIS DELIBERATION       
DOESN'T BODE WELL               
FOR THE PROSECUTION,            


390
00:29:17,089 --> 00:29:20,924
ESPECIALLY IN LIGHT OF THE FACT 
THAT THEY STILL HAVEN'T PRODUCED
THE MURDER WEAPON.              


391
00:29:20,992 --> 00:29:24,761
THE MURDER WEAPON.              
THE MURDER WEAPON.              
PRODUCED THE MURDER WEAPON.     


392
00:29:24,830 --> 00:29:26,963
        YEAH. I WONDER WHY.     


393
00:29:29,801 --> 00:29:31,735
<i>[ Knocking ]</i>                    


394
00:29:33,639 --> 00:29:37,441
        BRADLEY, WILL YOU       
        CHECK MY BRIEF FOR      
        THE WHITTAKER HEARING?  


395
00:29:37,510 --> 00:29:40,444
        I WORKED                
        FROM YOUR OLD APPEAL,   
        AND I MADE A FEW NOTES. 


396
00:29:40,513 --> 00:29:44,214
            YOU WHAT?           
    I WENT OVER                 
    THE OLD CASE FILE.          


397
00:29:44,283 --> 00:29:47,751
THERE'S SOME AREAS              
WE SHOULD EXPLORE.              
            NO, THERE AREN'T!   


398
00:29:50,389 --> 00:29:54,557
    COPY MY DRAFT!              
    CHANGE THE DATE.            
    STAMP MY SIGNATURE ON IT.   


399
00:29:54,626 --> 00:29:57,961
            GET IT TO THE COURT 
            BY 5:00.            


400
00:29:58,030 --> 00:30:02,066
    IF YOU CAN'T HANDLE THAT,   
    I'LL HIRE A MONKEY WHO CAN. 


401
00:30:06,638 --> 00:30:09,639
            SURE THING, BRAD.   
    [ Whirring ]                


402
00:30:17,649 --> 00:30:20,117
                SHOOT.          
                DAMN IT!        


403
00:30:30,896 --> 00:30:33,496
<i>[ Car Door Closes ]</i>             


404
00:30:33,565 --> 00:30:37,233
DON'T FIGHT IT, BROTHER.        


405
00:30:37,302 --> 00:30:40,236
AT TIMES LIKE THIS,             
A MAN'S GOTTA BELIEVE IN FATE.  


406
00:30:40,305 --> 00:30:43,240
<i>BAD LUCK,</i>                       


407
00:30:43,309 --> 00:30:45,309
MEET GOOD FORTUNE.              


408
00:30:47,446 --> 00:30:49,379
<i>MY CHARIOT.</i>                     


409
00:31:00,058 --> 00:31:03,393
<i>[ Whittaker ] I GOT A LETTER</i>    
<i>FROM MY MOM. SHE'S REALLY SICK.</i> 
<i>SHE SHOULDN'T BE ALONE.</i>         


410
00:31:03,461 --> 00:31:07,497
        DON'T WORRY, MARCUS.    
        YOU'RE GOING TO SEE     
        YOUR MOTHER AGAIN SOON. 


411
00:31:07,565 --> 00:31:11,601
    I PROMISE. BUT FIRST,       
    WE HAVE TO GO TO COURT...   


412
00:31:11,670 --> 00:31:13,736
            ONE MORE TIME.      


413
00:31:13,805 --> 00:31:17,907
                MR. SLOANE WILL 
                BE THERE TOO.   
WHAT DO I HAVE TO DO?           


414
00:31:17,976 --> 00:31:20,109
                TRUST ME.       


415
00:31:22,681 --> 00:31:26,049
<i>[ Isaac ]</i>                       
<i>SO, HOW WAS YOUR LUNCH MEETING?</i> 
<i>[ Dumont Chuckles ]</i>             


416
00:31:26,117 --> 00:31:28,619
EXTREMELY PROFITABLE.           


417
00:31:28,687 --> 00:31:31,888
ARRIVING IN THIS LIMO           
DIDN'T HURT NEGOTIATIONS EITHER.


418
00:31:36,661 --> 00:31:40,564
    EXCUSE ME. UM, SIR,         
    THIS ISN'T THE WAY          
    BACK TO THE OFFICE.         


419
00:31:40,633 --> 00:31:44,968
IT'S SUCH A FABULOUS DAY,       
I THOUGHT WE'D TAKE             
A LITTLE<i> RIDE.</i>                  


420
00:31:45,037 --> 00:31:48,372
                <i> [ Chuckling ]</i>  
        A RIDE?                 


421
00:31:48,440 --> 00:31:50,373
        TO-- TO WHERE?          


422
00:31:50,442 --> 00:31:53,744
    [ Laughing ]                
                        <i> HEY!</i>   


423
00:31:53,812 --> 00:31:56,046
<i>[ Doors Locking ]</i>               


424
00:31:56,114 --> 00:31:58,148
        WHAT THE--              


425
00:32:11,063 --> 00:32:15,498
<i>IN THE MATTER OF</i>                
BEAUMONT VS. MARKSWATCH--       


426
00:32:15,567 --> 00:32:18,268
            JAROD.              


427
00:32:18,337 --> 00:32:20,770
    I WANTED TO CONGRATULATE YOU
    ON THE WHITTAKER APPEAL.    


428
00:32:20,839 --> 00:32:24,675
<i>DUMONT SAYS THAT THE NEW TRIAL</i>  
<i>IS A SLAM DUNK.</i>                 
        NEW TRIAL?              


429
00:32:24,743 --> 00:32:27,844
    THE COURT HAS ACCEPTED      
    DUMONT'S MOTION TO          
    PRESENT NEW EVIDENCE.       


430
00:32:27,913 --> 00:32:29,780
        EVIDENCE?               


431
00:32:29,848 --> 00:32:33,115
YES, HE'S CONFIDENT THAT        
HE'S GONNA HAVE A WARRANT FOR   
THE MURDER WEAPON BY TOMORROW.  


432
00:32:33,184 --> 00:32:36,086
            HE DIDN'T TELL YOU? 


433
00:32:36,155 --> 00:32:38,721
<i>[ Intercom Beeps ]</i>              
    ANNIE, WHERE'S DUMONT?      


434
00:32:38,790 --> 00:32:40,723
<i>[ Annie ]</i>                       
<i>HE'S BEEN OUT ALL AFTERNOON.</i>    


435
00:32:40,792 --> 00:32:43,826
THE LAST I HEARD, HE WAS HAVING 
LUNCH WITH IRA KLEIN,           
THE CRIMINAL ATTORNEY--         


436
00:32:43,895 --> 00:32:48,431
            I KNOW WHO HE IS!   
            ANNIE!              


437
00:32:48,500 --> 00:32:51,101
        <i> [ Muttering, Shouting ]</i>


438
00:32:51,169 --> 00:32:53,603
    I WANNA KNOW                
    WHERE THE HELL DUMONT IS!   


439
00:32:53,672 --> 00:32:56,006
<i>[ Dumont ]</i>                      
<i>HEY, PAL, THIS IS KIDNAPPING.</i>   


440
00:32:56,074 --> 00:32:59,142
<i>♪♪ [ Blues ]</i>                    
    I'M A VERY SUCCESSFUL       
    ATTORNEY, YOU KNOW.         


441
00:32:59,210 --> 00:33:01,644
UH-UH-UH-UH-UH.                 


442
00:33:01,714 --> 00:33:06,449
THAT'S GONNA COST YOU           
ANOTHER HUNDRED MILES, ESQUIRE. 
[ Laughing ]                    


443
00:33:06,518 --> 00:33:08,518
                        <i> WHOO!</i>  


444
00:33:47,459 --> 00:33:50,694
<i>[ Sloane ]</i>                      
<i>MR. METZGER WAS WITH ME</i>         
<i>ON MY BOAT WHEN WORD REACHED--</i>  


445
00:33:52,965 --> 00:33:55,499
<i>MR. METZGER WAS WITH ME</i>         
<i>ON MY BOAT WHEN WORD REACHED--</i>  


446
00:33:58,170 --> 00:34:01,104
<i>[ Voice Distorted ]</i>             
<i>WITH ME ON MY BOAT.</i>             


447
00:34:11,717 --> 00:34:15,785
    HELLO. I WOULD LIKE TO BOOK 
    A NONSTOP FLIGHT            
    TO LOS ANGELES.             


448
00:34:23,028 --> 00:34:25,695
<i>[ Sloane ]</i>                      
<i>TELL THE ASSOCIATES</i>             
<i>THIS IS TOP PRIORITY.</i>           


449
00:34:25,764 --> 00:34:28,431
        <i> [ Keyboarding ]</i>        


450
00:34:30,636 --> 00:34:33,970
YES, I'D LIKE THE NUMBER        
FOR THE<i> LOS ANGELES CHRONICLE.</i>  


451
00:34:34,039 --> 00:34:36,139
        THE CITY DESK, PLEASE.  


452
00:34:42,447 --> 00:34:45,381
<i>[ Sloane ]</i>                      
<i>ANNIE, THERE'S SOMETHING</i>        
<i>I WANT YOU TO DO FOR ME.</i>        


453
00:34:45,451 --> 00:34:47,484
<i>[ Phone Ringing ]</i>               


454
00:34:49,087 --> 00:34:51,354
                HELLO?          


455
00:34:51,422 --> 00:34:53,890
            MR. SLOANE.         
            WELL, NO, SIR.      


456
00:34:53,959 --> 00:34:57,727
I WAS JUST LISTENING TO SOME    
VERY INTERESTING OLD RECORDINGS.


457
00:34:57,796 --> 00:35:00,597
        THE HEARING IS TOMORROW 
        AT 9:00 A.M.?           


458
00:35:00,665 --> 00:35:03,933
    YES, SIR, BUT SHOULDN'T     
    WE WAIT FOR MR. DUMONT?     


459
00:35:04,002 --> 00:35:07,103
            YES, SIR.           
            I UNDERSTAND.       


460
00:35:07,171 --> 00:35:09,506
    I'LL SEE YOU FIRST THING    
    TOMORROW MORNING.           


461
00:35:12,210 --> 00:35:14,777
            LIKE CLOCKWORK.     


462
00:35:14,846 --> 00:35:17,614
<i>[ Sloane ]</i>                      
<i>ANNIE, THERE'S SOMETHING</i>        
<i>I WANT YOU TO DO FOR ME.</i>        


463
00:35:26,024 --> 00:35:30,827
<i>ANNIE, TOP PRIORITY.</i>            
<i>THERE'S SOMETHING I WANT YOU</i>    
<i>TO DO FOR ME ON MY BOAT.</i>        


464
00:35:46,178 --> 00:35:48,511
            [ Tape Rewinding ]  


465
00:35:50,282 --> 00:35:54,484
    ANNIE, TOP PRIORITY.        
    THERE'S SOMETHING I WANT YOU
    TO DO FOR ME ON MY BOAT.    


466
00:35:55,820 --> 00:35:58,254
<i>[ Sloane ]</i>                      
<i>JUST WATCH, LISTEN</i>              
<i>AND LEARN, JAROD.</i>               


467
00:35:58,323 --> 00:36:01,191
    YOU WON'T SEE THIS KIND     
    OF DISMANTLING AGAIN SOON.  


468
00:36:01,260 --> 00:36:03,894
I'M LOOKING FORWARD             
TO IT, SIR.                     


469
00:36:03,962 --> 00:36:06,329
            WHAT ARE THE PRESS  
            DOING HERE?         


470
00:36:06,398 --> 00:36:10,333
        [ Reporters Clamoring ] 
    THERE'S NOTHING I CAN SAY   
    AT THIS POINT IN TIME.      


471
00:36:10,401 --> 00:36:13,536
BUT I WILL SAY THAT THERE'S     
GOING TO BE SOME SURPRISES.     


472
00:36:26,018 --> 00:36:28,718
        THE DISTRICT COURTHOUSE.
WHAT THE HELL?                  


473
00:36:28,787 --> 00:36:32,822
    YOU DIDN'T SERIOUSLY THINK  
    THE CENTRE WOULD CUT A DEAL 
    WITH JAROD?                 


474
00:36:34,426 --> 00:36:37,426
        DOUBLE DOUBLE CROSS,    
        SYD. IT'S JUST BUSINESS.


475
00:36:45,604 --> 00:36:47,537
HAVE A SEAT OVER THERE.         


476
00:36:49,540 --> 00:36:51,507
WHAT THE HELL                   
IS HE DOING HERE?               


477
00:36:51,576 --> 00:36:53,877
            I INVITED HIM.      


478
00:36:57,582 --> 00:37:00,083
<i>[ Judge ]</i>                       
<i>ON THE RECORD IN</i>                
PEOPLE VS. WHITTAKER,           


479
00:37:00,151 --> 00:37:02,885
THE COURT HEARING A DEFENSE     
MOTION TO PRESENT NEW EVIDENCE. 


480
00:37:02,954 --> 00:37:05,221
MR. HOLMES.                     


481
00:37:05,290 --> 00:37:08,457
<i>YOUR HONOR, MR. HOLMES</i>          
<i>IS A JUNIOR ASSOCIATE</i>           
<i>IN OUR FIRM.</i>                    


482
00:37:08,526 --> 00:37:10,459
HE DOESN'T REPRESENT            
THIS PARTICULAR CLIENT.         


483
00:37:10,528 --> 00:37:12,461
        WITH ALL DUE RESPECT,   
        YOUR HONOR,             
        I WROTE THE MOTION,     


484
00:37:12,530 --> 00:37:14,664
        AND I DID THE RESEARCH  
        FOR THIS HEARING.       


485
00:37:14,732 --> 00:37:18,902
TO ASSIGN IT TO ANOTHER ATTORNEY
IS TO DENY MARCUS WHITTAKER     
A CHANCE AT FAIR REPRESENTATION.


486
00:37:18,970 --> 00:37:21,571
WHAT THE HELL                   
DO YOU THINK YOU'RE DOING?      
TRYING TO GET AN INNOCENT MAN...


487
00:37:21,640 --> 00:37:23,873
        <i> A FAIR SHOT AT JUSTICE.</i>
    THAT'S ENOUGH.              


488
00:37:23,942 --> 00:37:28,377
<i>MR. WHITTAKER,</i>                  
<i>IS THERE AN ATTORNEY</i>            
<i>YOU'D LIKE TO REPRESENT YOU?</i>    


489
00:37:31,416 --> 00:37:33,349
                JAROD.          


490
00:37:33,418 --> 00:37:36,886
    - YOUR HONOR--              
    - IT'S OVER, MR. SLOANE.    


491
00:37:36,955 --> 00:37:38,888
CALL YOUR FIRST WITNESS,        
MR. HOLMES.                     


492
00:37:38,956 --> 00:37:41,291
                    <i> YOUR HONOR,</i>


493
00:37:41,359 --> 00:37:45,962
        THE DEFENSE CALLS       
        BENJAMIN SLOANE.        


494
00:37:46,031 --> 00:37:48,431
<i>[ People Chattering ]</i>           
            <i> [ Gavel Rapping ]</i>  


495
00:37:48,500 --> 00:37:52,602
<i>MR. SLOANE, YOU REPRESENTED</i>     
<i>MARCUS WHITTAKER TO THE VERY</i>    
<i>BEST OF YOUR ABILITY.</i>           


496
00:37:52,671 --> 00:37:55,604
        - IS THAT CORRECT?      
        - ABSOLUTELY.           


497
00:37:55,673 --> 00:37:58,808
AND TO THE BEST OF              
YOUR KNOWLEDGE, NOTHING         
SLIPPED THROUGH THE CRACKS?     


498
00:37:58,877 --> 00:38:02,612
    THERE ARE NO CRACKS         
    AT SLOANE AND ASSOCIATES.   
<i>HMM.</i>                            


499
00:38:02,681 --> 00:38:06,949
WOULD YOU EXPLAIN               
YOUR RELATIONSHIP               
WITH MICHAEL METZGER?           


500
00:38:09,187 --> 00:38:11,254
            HE'S A CLIENT.      


501
00:38:11,323 --> 00:38:13,556
WERE YOU AWARE THAT YOUR CLIENT 
WAS CARRYING ON AN AFFAIR...    


502
00:38:13,625 --> 00:38:16,225
WITH AUDREY PRICE               
AT THE TIME OF THE MURDER?      


503
00:38:16,294 --> 00:38:20,931
- DO YOU HAVE ANY PROOF OF THAT?
- MARCUS WHITTAKER WOULD GLADLY 
  TESTIFY TO IT UNDER OATH.     


504
00:38:20,999 --> 00:38:23,666
            WHAT'S YOUR POINT,  
            MR. HOLMES?         


505
00:38:23,735 --> 00:38:26,736
NOW YOU WENT THROUGH            
GREAT PAINS TO ESTABLISH        
THE FACT...                     


506
00:38:26,804 --> 00:38:31,007
THAT MICHAEL METZGER WAS A GUEST
ON YOUR BOAT AT THE TIME        
OF THE MURDER-- IS THAT CORRECT?


507
00:38:31,076 --> 00:38:34,811
        I WOULDN'T CALL IT      
        "GREAT PAINS."          
        HE WAS THERE.           


508
00:38:34,880 --> 00:38:37,179
DO YOU REMEMBER WHAT TIME       
AUDREY PRICE WAS KILLED?        


509
00:38:37,248 --> 00:38:42,986
        BETWEEN 9:00 AND 9:15,  
        IF MEMORY SERVES ME.    
<i>INTERESTING.</i>                    


510
00:38:43,055 --> 00:38:45,755
THEN MAYBE                      
YOU COULD TELL ME...            


511
00:38:45,823 --> 00:38:48,691
WHY MR. METZGER MADE            
A CELL PHONE CALL               
TO YOUR BOAT...                 


512
00:38:48,760 --> 00:38:54,430
AT 9:20 THE VERY SAME NIGHT     
IF HE WAS WITH YOU.             


513
00:38:54,498 --> 00:38:56,866
    MAY I SEE THAT, MR. HOLMES? 


514
00:39:01,773 --> 00:39:04,340
    PROCEED.                    


515
00:39:04,409 --> 00:39:08,511
FOR THE RECORD,                 
THE D.A. HAS CATALOGED          
THIS PHOTO...                   


516
00:39:08,579 --> 00:39:11,948
AS A PARTIAL SHOE PRINT         
FROM THE MURDER SCENE.          


517
00:39:12,016 --> 00:39:15,718
MR. SLOANE, WOULD YOU EXPLAIN   
TO THE COURT WHY THE JURY       
NEVER SAW THIS PHOTOGRAPH?      


518
00:39:15,787 --> 00:39:18,989
        <i> THE POLICE NEVER MADE</i>  
        <i> A POSITIVE MATCH.</i>      


519
00:39:19,057 --> 00:39:21,124
        IT PROVED NOTHING.      


520
00:39:21,192 --> 00:39:24,794
        WELL, PERHAPS I COULD   
        HELP THE POLICE OUT.    


521
00:39:24,862 --> 00:39:27,964
IT'S A SIZE 11, DECK SHOE.      


522
00:39:28,033 --> 00:39:32,068
<i>YOU WERE ON YOUR BOAT</i>           
<i>THAT NIGHT, WEREN'T YOU,</i>        
<i>MR. SLOANE?</i>                     


523
00:39:32,136 --> 00:39:35,738
    [ Chuckles ]                
    SO, NOW I'M THE KILLER?     
<i>NO.</i>                             


524
00:39:35,807 --> 00:39:38,141
YOU WERE THE JANITOR.           


525
00:39:38,209 --> 00:39:42,011
WE'LL GET TO THE KILLER.        
        YOUR HONOR, THIS IS     
        POINTLESS HARASSMENT.   


526
00:39:42,080 --> 00:39:44,213
                <i> [ Judge ]</i>      
                <i> MR. HOLMES.</i>    
<i>[ Door Closes ]</i>                 


527
00:39:44,282 --> 00:39:46,082
        ONE MOMENT, PLEASE.     


528
00:39:50,889 --> 00:39:53,256
<i>[ Annie ]</i>                       
<i>MR. SLOANE'S ON TRIAL?</i>          
<i>NOT OFFICIALLY.</i>                 


529
00:39:53,325 --> 00:39:55,891
                NOT YET, ANYWAY.


530
00:40:02,333 --> 00:40:04,267
        <i> [ Banging Desk ]</i>       


531
00:40:04,335 --> 00:40:06,435
<i>I LOVE THIS PART.</i>               


532
00:40:07,773 --> 00:40:11,908
        A SIZE 11 DECK SHOE...  


533
00:40:11,977 --> 00:40:14,076
    FROM MR. SLOANE'S CLOSET.   


534
00:40:14,145 --> 00:40:16,712
        - PROVES NOTHING.       
        -<i> NO.</i>                   


535
00:40:16,781 --> 00:40:18,781
        BUT THIS CERTAINLY DOES.


536
00:40:22,253 --> 00:40:24,587
        THE MURDER WEAPON.      


537
00:40:24,655 --> 00:40:26,789
<i>STAINED WITH</i>                    
<i>THE VICTIM'S BLOOD.</i>             


538
00:40:26,858 --> 00:40:29,425
MR. SLOANE, WOULD YOU CARE      
TO EXPLAIN TO THE COURT...      


539
00:40:29,494 --> 00:40:33,462
    WHAT THE LONG-LOST          
    MURDER WEAPON WAS DOING     
    ON YOUR BOAT?               


540
00:40:33,531 --> 00:40:35,932
        [ Scoffs ]              
        THIS IS RIDICULOUS.     


541
00:40:36,001 --> 00:40:38,667
    I DON'T THINK THAT          
    MICHAEL METZGER THINKS SO.  


542
00:40:38,736 --> 00:40:42,872
YOU'VE BEEN BLACKMAILING HIM    
WITH THIS SINCE                 
THE MURDER TRIAL.               


543
00:40:44,375 --> 00:40:46,876
MICHAEL METZGER BEAT            
AUDREY PRICE TO DEATH.          


544
00:40:46,945 --> 00:40:50,280
<i>AND THEN HE CALLED UPON</i>         
<i>MR. SLOANE TO CLEAN UP THE MESS.</i>


545
00:40:50,348 --> 00:40:54,317
<i>ONLY BEFORE YOU GOT THERE,</i>      
<i>MR. WHITTAKER ARRIVED.</i>          


546
00:40:55,821 --> 00:40:58,387
HE FOUND THE VICTIM.            
 HE PANICKED.                   


547
00:40:58,456 --> 00:41:00,890
HE RAN AWAY.                    


548
00:41:00,959 --> 00:41:04,260
YOU ALLOWED AN INNOCENT MAN     
TO GO TO JAIL.                  


549
00:41:06,331 --> 00:41:09,265
<i>IF I'VE MISSED SOMETHING,</i>       
<i>FEEL FREE TO JUMP IN.</i>           


550
00:41:11,002 --> 00:41:14,637
    <i> YOUR HONOR, THERE HASN'T</i>   
    <i> BEEN A PIECE OF EVIDENCE...</i>


551
00:41:14,706 --> 00:41:18,241
        PRESENTED HERE THAT     
        A GOOD DEFENSE ATTORNEY 
        COULDN'T SHOOT DOWN.    


552
00:41:18,310 --> 00:41:20,943
    THEN I SUGGEST              
    YOU FIND A VERY GOOD ONE.   


553
00:41:21,012 --> 00:41:24,314
<i>I'M ORDERING YOU INTO CUSTODY</i>   
<i>AS AN ACCESSORY TO MURDER...</i>    


554
00:41:24,382 --> 00:41:27,650
<i>AND ISSUING A BENCH WARRANT</i>     
<i>FOR THE ARREST OF</i>               
<i>MICHAEL METZGER.</i>                


555
00:41:27,718 --> 00:41:30,186
            <i> COURT ADJOURNED.</i>   
                <i> [ Gavel Raps ]</i> 


556
00:41:30,255 --> 00:41:33,022
I DON'T KNOW WHAT KIND OF LAW   
YOU'RE PRACTICING HERE.         


557
00:41:33,091 --> 00:41:37,093
THE KIND OF LAW THAT APPLIES    
TO MILLIONAIRES TOO.            


558
00:41:41,566 --> 00:41:45,300
<i>CONGRATULATIONS, MARCUS.</i>        
<i>YOU'RE A FREE MAN.</i>              


559
00:42:00,551 --> 00:42:03,819
        GO, SAM. WE'LL HEAD     
        HIM OFF DOWNSTAIRS.     


560
00:42:06,624 --> 00:42:09,158
        [ Monitor Beeping ]     
HEY, HOLD IT RIGHT THERE!       


561
00:42:09,226 --> 00:42:12,628
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.           
I HAVE A PERMIT TO CARRY THAT.  


562
00:42:15,433 --> 00:42:18,400
        EXCUSE ME. EXCUSE ME.   
        OUT OF MY WAY!          


563
00:42:20,238 --> 00:42:22,671
    THAT WAY.                   


564
00:42:22,740 --> 00:42:25,074
JAROD!                          


565
00:42:56,307 --> 00:42:58,308
            DAMN IT!            


566
00:43:00,812 --> 00:43:04,514
    NEXT TIME I'M JUST GONNA    
    SHOOT THE LITTLE PAIN       
    IN THE ASS.                 


567
00:43:18,863 --> 00:43:21,698
<i>[ Horn Honking ]</i>                


568
00:43:21,766 --> 00:43:24,633
<i>GET IN THE CAR.</i>                 


569
00:43:27,538 --> 00:43:30,139
    <i> [ Engine Not Turning Over ]</i>


570
00:43:43,688 --> 00:43:46,188
    RIGHT THIS WAY,             
    MR. METZGER.                


571
00:43:46,257 --> 00:43:49,559
        LOOK, I WANNA SEE       
        MY ATTORNEY, ALL RIGHT? 


572
00:43:49,627 --> 00:43:52,828
        I SAID, I WANNA SEE     
        MY ATTORNEY!            


573
00:43:52,897 --> 00:43:55,030
                [ Policeman ]   
                YOU'RE IN LUCK. 


574
00:44:02,006 --> 00:44:04,273
        <i> [ Gate Alarm Buzzing ]</i> 


575
00:44:13,084 --> 00:44:15,017
[ Woman ]                       
EXCUSE ME.                      


576
00:44:18,022 --> 00:44:19,956
<i>[ Whistling ]</i>                   


577
00:44:32,737 --> 00:44:34,470
                    MOM!        


578
00:44:34,539 --> 00:44:37,774
            [ Laughing ]        


579
00:44:37,842 --> 00:44:40,009
            HOW'D YOU GET HERE? 


580
00:44:40,078 --> 00:44:42,144
        A MAN SENT ME A TICKET. 


581
00:44:50,121 --> 00:44:52,321
<i>[ Mom ]</i>                         
<i>WHAT IS IT?</i>                     


582
00:44:53,458 --> 00:44:55,391
IT'S A PAPER CLOCK.             


583
00:44:57,728 --> 00:45:01,863
    "NOW YOU HAVE ALL THE TIME  
     IN THE WORLD.              


584
00:45:01,932 --> 00:45:04,867
        "CHERISH YOUR FREEDOM,  
         MARCUS.                


585
00:45:04,936 --> 00:45:07,369
        YOUR PEN PAL, JAROD."   


586
00:45:17,482 --> 00:45:19,415
HOLD ON TO IT NOW.              
RIGHT THERE.                    


587
00:45:19,484 --> 00:45:21,818
<i>YOU ALL RIGHT?</i>                  
                <i> [ Jarod ]</i>      
                <i> EIGHT SECONDS?</i> 


588
00:45:21,886 --> 00:45:23,720
                    THAT'S IT?  
        UH-HUH.                 


589
00:45:23,788 --> 00:45:26,855
- EIGHT SECONDS? EIGHT SECONDS? 
- [ Lowing ]                    


590
00:45:28,293 --> 00:45:31,427
    - LET HER RIP.              
    -<i> [ Alarm Sounding ]</i>        


591
00:45:31,495 --> 00:45:36,031
<i>[ Announcer ] HO! WATCH THAT</i>    
<i>BULL FLY RIGHT OUT OF THERE,</i>    
<i>LADIES AND GENTLEMEN!</i>           


592
00:45:36,100 --> 00:45:38,501
<i>WHAT A RIDE!</i>                    


593
00:46:11,202 --> 00:46:12,201
            [ Mews ]            


